Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "kavu" (кофу) in different forms and positions with translations in English in parentheses:

1. *Kavu* je trebalo da bacimo u smeće. (We needed to throw *the bucket* away in the trash.)
2. Nisam stigao da operem *kavu*. (I didn't have time to wash *the bucket*.)
3. *Kava* koju pravim u ovoj *kavi* je jaka. (The *coffee* I make in this *coffee pot* is strong.)
4. Ova *kava* nije dovoljno topla. (This *coffee* is not hot enough.)
5. *Kavi* koju si kupio fali drška. (The *bucket* you bought is missing a handle.)
6. Da li mi možeš dati *kavu*? (Can you give me *the bucket*?)
7. *Kavu* sam napunio vodom. (I filled *the bucket* with water.)
8. *Kava* se prosula po podu. (The *coffee* spilled on the floor.)
9. Hteo sam da kupim *kavu*, ali su sve bile rasprodane. (I wanted to buy *buckets*, but they were all sold out.)
10. *Kava* je bila teška za nošenje. (The *bucket* was heavy to carry.)